Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and salt in a small bowl until well combined. Blend in peanut butter and butter with a fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Spray a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round microwave-safe baking dish with a no-stick spray. Place apples in prepared dish. Top with oat mixture. Microwave 14 to 16 minutes, turning dish 1/4 turn halfway through cook time, if necessary. Serve warm with cream or ice cream.